column5: For those of you who are dying for ice, here's a little taste. Today in Port:        It's early and it's just a tease but what the hell.....
and here I am thinking of putting the boat in scugog in a week or so
Based on the two week forecast you're probably still good to go.
feeling confident. Although if winds actually behave this time I likely go to St Clair
Mon, Tues, Wed this week are 6*C, 11*C, and 9*C respectively. Id think the ice wouldn't last in three days of that. That's for Port Perry.
A little wind will take that away.
think i can take my new truck out for a fish?  After this week the temps drop back down and then it gets real cold...lookout pikeys!
With no walleye will anyone fish Scugog this winter? Will you?
^^^ I might try for panfish on Scugog.  Just because it's close. Walleye was shut down last winter and there were still people fishing.
Its loaded with crappies. Easy to catch a feed through the ice.  S.
